race.comment: NIGHTLINE (11) produced a nice effort on debut in better company last start over 1200m at Gold Coast when second, beaten a head. Has plenty of upside so she will prove tough to beat. LADY WINDERMERE (10) is resuming after a spell of five months. Closed last campaign with a fourth over this journey at Gold Coast, beaten 0.7 lengths. Fitter for two trials, placing most recently. Looks set for a bright return. UNIQUELY FAMOUS (7) is a Toronado gelding on debut for the dominant Chris Waller stable. Fitter for a recent trial and gets the key booking of Wiggins. Blinkers are on, expect him to be very competitive. VINTAGE VIBES (14) returns and looks to have come on nicely during the break on the back of some nice trial performances. Draws to get the gun run from the inside pillar and can make the perfect return. AN DE BAN (8) showed improvement second-up when closing off nicely into fifth. Backs up quickly and is open to further improvement. Holds claims.
